<title>Washington University Computer Science Department</title>


<!WA0><img alt = "Washington University Department of Computer Science" src =
"http://www.cs.wustl.edu/cs/images/cs_logo.gif">

<body background="/cs/images/background.gif">
<p>

<!WA1><img align=left vspace=10 hspace=20 src="http://www.cs.wustl.edu/cs/images/fiskegde.gif">
<p>
1997 Fiske Guide to Colleges names Computer Science among the strongest ten programs
at Washington University.<br clear=left>
<p>

<b><!WA2><a href = "http://aix.cait.wustl.edu/">
Saint Louis</a></b> offers the Washington University student beautiful 
surroundings and easy access to the resources of a great metropolitan 
area recognized for its quality of life.<p>

<b><!WA3><a href = "http://www.wustl.edu/">Washington University</a></b>,
one of the top twenty national universities, is a leading research 
institution proud to have been associated with twenty
Nobel laureates, two U. S. Poets Laureate, and numerous other creative minds.
<p>

<b><!WA4><a href = "http://www.cs.wustl.edu/cs/intro.html">
The Computer Science Department</a></b>
is part of the <b><!WA5><a href = "http://www.ecl.wustl.edu/seas/">School
of Engineering and Applied Science</a></b>.  Medium-sized, close-knit, 
well-equipped, and spacious, the 
department is experiencing an exciting period of growth manifest in
<ul>
<li> <!WA6><a href = "http://www.cs.wustl.edu/cs/labs.html">cutting-edge research</a> 
     in areas of significant current import
<li> <!WA7><a href = "http://www.cs.wustl.edu/cs/funding.html">
     major research funding</a> 
     from both industry and government
<li> <!WA8><a href = "http://www.cs.wustl.edu/cs/publications.html">
     impressive publication record</a> in leading journals
<li> <!WA9><a href = "http://www.cs.wustl.edu/cs/placement.html">
     successful placement</a> of recent graduates
</ul>
<p>

After five years of service as Department Chair, Jon Turner is stepping
down to devote his time to research and teaching activities.  The Department
is conducting a nationwide search for highly qualified candidates 
interested in the 
<!WA10><a href="http://www.cs.wustl.edu/cs/chairposition.html">
chair position</a>.
<p>

New courses for Fall 1996:
<ul>
<li> <!WA11><a href = "http://cs.wustl.edu/cs/courses.html#300">    CS 300:   The Art and Science of Computing
</a>
<li> <!WA12><a href = "http://cs.wustl.edu/cs/courses.html">    CS 242S:  Object-Oriented Software Design
</a>
<li> <!WA13><a href = "http://cs.wustl.edu/cs/courses.html">    CS 333S:  Distributed Applications
</a>
<li> <!WA14><a href = "http://cs.wustl.edu/cs/courses.html">CS 516A:  Multiagent Systems
</a>
</ul>

<p>



